{
  "texts": [
    "However, due to the absence of a cohesive national strategy and gaps in connecting societal needs and teachers' development, STEM education is still in its early development phase in China (Han and Appelbaum, 2018a, 2018b).",
    "This early stage of development presents challenges and opportunities, particularly in aligning teacher training with the evolving educational landscape.",
    "Cultivating an educational atmosphere that embraces STEM is crucial, including creating varied and resource-rich school curricula (Yang and Gao, 2021).",
    "Each school must develop resources, such as infrastructure and software, to reflect its local strengths and subject matter (Ananda et al. 2023).",
    "Teachers need to improve their technological and pedagogical skills as part of their professional development (Chai et al. 2020; Iqbal et al. 2022)."
  ]
}